            <scopecontent id="aspace_f3f940c9c33aa1d1057d8ee9b05ee0cd">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The series holds autograph manuscripts and typescripts of Elizabeth MacKinstry's poems, most of which she bound in paperboard binders with decorations inside their covers. Also present is a copy of <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Helen's Mirror and Other Verses</part>
                  </title> (London: Elkin Mathews, 1913), a small volume of poems MacKinstry published under her pseudonym Elizabeth Westermain; it was part of the publisher's "Savile" series of poetry books. Ephemera includes transcribed and clipped published reviews of MacKinstry's books and a postcard advertising an exhibition of MacKinstry's work in 1957.</p>
            </scopecontent>
